    {
      "id": "9fd19b4857a798a42e89e09667ae3ff66f0b9843",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 116,
        "name": "Brian J. Murrell",
        "email": "brian.murrell@intel.com",
        "username": "brian",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2014-03-27 10:31:07.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n(6 comments)\n\nGenerally, while it seems the goal of this patch is to just change the default behaviour to not build liblustre but leave it buildable if desired, the changes to the debian build seems pretty non-optional and remove any way to get a liblustre .deb.  Does that really square with the intention?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "d7c5523b1c3ce7af565612934d600704ca14a75c",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 177,
        "name": "John Hammond",
        "email": "jhammond@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jhammond"
      },
      "date": "2014-03-27 19:49:18.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nBrian, I don't see any reason to keep the *.deb. My reasoning was as follows:\n\n1. It doesn't work now.\n\n2. It's not going to work in the future.\n\n3. Even if it did work, it won't work well.\n\n4. A Ubuntu system should use the lustre client modules, not liblustre.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "6c70cbe84eaa963a08b4fb7a88da4a9eee67b6c4",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 116,
        "name": "Brian J. Murrell",
        "email": "brian.murrell@intel.com",
        "username": "brian",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2014-03-28 11:46:18.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> 1. It doesn't work now.\n\nliblustre or the .deb building?\n\n> 2. It's not going to work in the future.\n\nDitto.\n\n> 3. Even if it did work, it won't work well.\n\nAgain, ditto.\n\n> 4. A Ubuntu system should use the lustre client modules, not liblustre\n\nUltimately the problem is the mixed goal here.  Is the goal to completely remove liblustre (because as you might be saying above: 1. it doesn't work now, 2. it won't work in the future and 3. won't work well) or just to disable it by default?\n\nBecause the intention of everything (except the .deb building) seems to be to just disable it by default but leave it there for anyone who wants to build it.  But in the same stroke you are completely removing the ability to build .deb even if one opts for it.\n\nSo it seems to me that if you want to disable it by default, then do that across the board.  If you want to remove it completely and not even make it an option any more then do that -- across the board.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "d3eabfa74325fdb86f22b44d3ab5ebc384fd4756",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 177,
        "name": "John Hammond",
        "email": "jhammond@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jhammond"
      },
      "date": "2014-03-28 18:44:34.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> liblustre or the .deb building?\n\nliblustre\n\n> Ultimately the problem is the mixed goal here. Is the goal to completely remove liblustre (because as you might be saying above: 1. it doesn't work now, 2. it won't work in the future and 3. won't work well) or just to disable it by default?\n\nOK. Can you suggest how to disable building the liblustre deb? Without removing it.\n\nThe goal is for us to expend less energy on liblustre for no return.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
