    {
      "id": "81fc7d04a0b3b92d3a3fa8969b73366cdd3f7858",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 116,
        "name": "Brian J. Murrell",
        "email": "brian.murrell@intel.com",
        "username": "brian",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2014-04-01 11:01:29.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\n> OK. Can you suggest how to disable building the liblustre deb? Without removing it.\n\nHave you tried just removing the liblustre binary target in the rules makefile from binary-arch target without removing any of the other liblustre .deb bits in /debian?  Determining if that's sufficient is a first step.  If it is, then having the liblustre target in the binary-arch target being conditional is the only change you have to make.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "22776a8edf2f97bebcdd92dcba126c7e31180ba2",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 177,
        "name": "John Hammond",
        "email": "jhammond@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jhammond"
      },
      "date": "2014-04-15 19:01:47.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nBrian, the goal is to remove it completely. But that can't be accomplished in a single patch. Could you take a second look with this in mind?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "abdb4cebda475555541035d25c147754a8360388",
      "author": {
